<react-component-organization>

<title>React Component Organization</title>

<rules>
- Keep React components under 200 lines of code
- Extract complex logic into custom hooks when component approaches 150 lines
- Place custom hooks in separate files within the same directory
- Colocate test files with components using `.test.tsx` or `.spec.tsx` suffix
- Use the pattern: `ComponentName.tsx` and `ComponentName.test.tsx` in the same folder
- Extract reusable hooks to a shared `hooks/` directory when used by multiple components
- Split large components into smaller sub-components when they handle multiple concerns
- Keep component files focused on rendering logic and UI state
</rules>

<examples>
<example type="good">
```
src/
  components/
    UserProfile/
      UserProfile.tsx          // Under 200 lines
      UserProfile.test.tsx     // Tests colocated
      useUserData.ts          // Extracted hook
      UserAvatar.tsx          // Sub-component
      UserAvatar.test.tsx     // Sub-component tests
```
</example>
</examples>

